Shutter Island is a great movie that will keep
Most people guessing until the end. It's a psychological thriller better then most that I have seen. When I was in nursing school, I was able to use it for a paper in mental health nursing. I know that I have watched it several times with different people, and some did not understand the ending. Every detail matters.

These are two great Leonardo DiCaprio movies. Shutter Island is a great thriller, but The Aviator is a modern day classic. DiCaprio simply becomes Howard Hughes and should have won the Oscar for his performance. In The Aviator, DiCaprio proves that he is the best actor of his generation.

Forgetting the incredible value of this blue package the films are quite obviously evidence of genius. In my opinion nobody ever has or ever will make films like Scorsese. His style is so unique far beyond the Hitchcock esque style of Spielberg or any of his contemporaries Scorsese will go done as the greatest director.
